name: Pineco
flavorText: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn't bother it.

name: Forretress ex
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 5 Basic Grass Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck. If you searched your deck in this way, this Pokémon is Knocked Out.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Maractus
flavorText: Once each year, this Pokémon scatters its seeds. They're jam-packed with nutrients, making them a precious food source out in the desert.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

name: Toedscool
flavorText: Though it looks like Tentacool, Toedscool is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Toedscruel ex
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks used by your opponent's Pokémon done to all of your Pokémon that have Energy attached. (Existing effects are not removed. Damage is not an effect.)
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon that has any Grass Energy attached.

name: Espathra ex
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, attacks used by your opponent's Active Pokémon cost Colorless more.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to both Active Pokémon.

name: Charmander
flavorText: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.
Attack1Text: Discard a Stadium in play.

name: Charmeleon
flavorText: If it becomes agitated during battle, it spouts intense flames, incinerating its surroundings.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks used by your opponent's Pokémon done to this Pokémon. (Damage is not an effect.)

name: Magmar
flavorText: These Pokémon's bodies are constantly burning. Magmar are feared as one of the causes behind fires.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Magmortar
flavorText: Living in the crater of a volcano has caused this Pokémon's body to resemble its environment— it has an organ similar to a magma chamber.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Numel
flavorText: Magma of almost 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. When it grows cold, the magma hardens and slows it.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Camerupt
flavorText: It lives in the crater of a volcano. It is well known that the humps on its back erupt every 10 years.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: You may discard a Fighting Energy from this Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Heat Rotom
flavorText: If the convection microwave oven is not working properly, then the Rotom inhabiting it will become lethargic.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 40 damage to itself.

name: Charcadet
flavorText: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokémon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.

name: Armarouge
flavorText: Armarouge evolved through the use of a set of armor that belonged to a distinguished warrior. This Pokémon is incredibly loyal.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may move a Fire Energy from 1 of your Benched Pokémon to your Active Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Lapras
flavorText: Crossing icy seas is no issue for this cold-resistant Pokémon. Its smooth skin is a little cool to the touch.
Attack1Text: Put up to 3 Basic Energy cards from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Frigibax
flavorText: Frigibax absorbs heat through its dorsal fin and converts the heat into ice energy. The higher the temperature, the more energy Frigibax stores.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: ﻿When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon's attacks do 20 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Raichu
flavorText: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.
Ability1Text: When 1 of your Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, you may move a Lightning Energy from that Pokémon to this Pokémon.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 50 damage to itself.

name: Chinchou
flavorText: On the dark ocean floor, its only means of communication is its constantly flashing lights.
Attack1Text: Look at the top card of your deck. You may put that card on the bottom of your deck.

name: Lanturn
flavorText: This Pokémon flashes a bright light that blinds its prey. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electrical attack.
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon has any Water Energy attached, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Kilowattrel
flavorText: Kilowattrel inflates its throat sac to amplify its electricity. By riding the wind, this Pokémon can fly over 430 miles in a day.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile that has the United Wings attack to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Exeggcute
flavorText: These Pokémon get nervous when they're not in a group of six. The minute even one member of the group goes missing, Exeggcute become cowardly.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Exeggutor
flavorText: When they work together, Exeggutor's three heads can put out powerful psychic energy. Cloudy days make this Pokémon sluggish.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Put 2 Energy attached to this Pokémon into your hand.

name: Natu
flavorText: Because its wings aren't yet fully grown, it has to hop to get around. It is always staring at something.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Xatu
flavorText: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun's movement all day.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Basic Psychic Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. If you attached Energy to a Pokémon in this way, draw 2 cards.

name: Ralts
flavorText: The horns on its head provide a strong power that enables it to sense people's emotions.

name: Kirlia
flavorText: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Gardevoir ex
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may attach a Basic Psychic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Psychic Pokémon. If you attached Energy to a Pokémon in this way, put 2 damage counters on that Pokémon. You can't use this Ability on a Pokémon that would be Knocked Out.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon recovers from all Special Conditions.

name: Chimecho
flavorText: Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.
Attack1Text: Switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot. The new Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Mime Jr.
flavorText: In an attempt to confuse its enemy, it mimics the enemy's movements. Then it wastes no time in making itself scarce!
Attack1Text: Your opponent chooses an attack from 1 of their Pokémon in play. Use the chosen attack as this attack.

name: Woobat
flavorText: It emits ultrasonic waves as it flutters about, searching for its prey—bug Pokémon.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Swoobat
flavorText: The auspicious shape of this Pokémon's nose apparently led some regions to consider Swoobat a symbol of good luck.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused. Put 6 damage counters instead of 3 on that Pokémon for this Special Condition.

name: Cottonee
flavorText: Weaving together the cotton of both Cottonee and Eldegoss produces exquisite cloth that's highly prized by many luxury brands.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Whimsicott
flavorText: As long as this Pokémon bathes in sunlight, its cotton keeps growing. If too much cotton fluff builds up, Whimsicott tears it off and scatters it.

name: Dedenne
flavorText: It's small and its electricity-generating organ is not fully developed, so it uses its tail to absorb electricity from people's homes and charge itself.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Mimikyu
flavorText: This Pokémon lives in dark places untouched by sunlight. When it appears before humans, it hides itself under a cloth that resembles a Pikachu.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon ex and Pokémon V.
Attack1Text: Put 7 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Fidough
flavorText: This Pokémon is smooth and moist to the touch. Yeast in Fidough's breath induces fermentation in the Pokémon's vicinity.

name: Dachsbun
flavorText: The pleasant aroma that emanates from this Pokémon's body helps wheat grow, so Dachsbun has been treasured by farming villages.
Ability1Text: This Pokémon can't be Burned. Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Fire Pokémon.

name: Ceruledge
flavorText: The fiery blades on its arms burn fiercely with the lingering resentment of a sword wielder who fell before accomplishing their goal.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex or Pokémon V, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Flittle
flavorText: Flittle's toes levitate about half an inch above the ground because of the psychic power emitted from the frills on the Pokémon's belly.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Greavard
flavorText: This friendly Pokémon doesn't like being alone. Pay it even the slightest bit of attention, and it will follow you forever.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage for each Psychic Pokémon in your discard pile.

name: Houndstone
flavorText: A lovingly mourned Pokémon was reborn as Houndstone. It doesn't like anyone touching the protuberance atop its head.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each Psychic Pokémon in your discard pile.

name: Gimmighoul
flavorText: This Pokémon was born inside a treasure chest about 1,500 years ago. It sucks the life-force out of scoundrels who try to steal the treasure.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Mankey
flavorText: It is extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment, then thrashing away the next instant.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Primeape
flavorText: Some researchers theorize that Primeape remains angry even when inside a Poké Ball.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

name: Annihilape
flavorText: It imbues its fists with the power of the rage that it kept hidden in its heart. Opponents struck by these imbued fists will be shattered to their core.
Attack1Text: This attack does 70 damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 50 damage to itself.

name: Phanpy
flavorText: This Pokémon lives and nests on a riverbank. After playing in the mud, it won't be able to settle down unless it washes its body.

name: Donphan
flavorText: Donphan is covered in tough hide, so even being hit by a car won't faze this Pokémon. However, it is extremely susceptible to rain.
Attack1Text: Discard the top 2 cards of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Barboach
flavorText: Its two whiskers provide a sensitive radar. Even in muddy waters, it can detect its prey's location.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Clobbopus
flavorText: Its tentacles tear off easily, but it isn't alarmed when that happens—it knows they'll grow back. It's about as smart as a three-year-old.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Grapploct
flavorText: Searching for an opponent to test its skills against, it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over, it returns to the sea.
Attack1Text: At the end of your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon will be Knocked Out.

name: Great Tusk ex
Ability1Text: Once at the end of your turn (after your attack), if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you must discard the top 5 cards of your deck.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Charizard ex
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 3 Basic Fire Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

name: Gastly
flavorText: It wraps its opponent in its gas-like body, slowly weakening its prey by poisoning it through the skin.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Haunter
flavorText: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Gengar
flavorText: To steal the life of its target, it slips into the prey's shadow and silently waits for an opportunity.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may switch your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Paldean Wooper
flavorText: After losing a territorial struggle, Wooper began living on land. The Pokémon changed over time, developing a poisonous film to protect its body.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Stadium card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Paldean Clodsire ex
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if a Stadium is in play, you may make your opponent's Active Pokémon Poisoned.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, during your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Scraggy
flavorText: It protects itself with its durable skin. It's thought that this Pokémon will evolve once its skin has completely stretched out.

name: Scrafty
flavorText: While mostly known for having the temperament of an aggressive ruffian, this Pokémon takes very good care of its family, friends, and territory.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Basic Pokémon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Maschiff
flavorText: It always scowls in an attempt to make opponents take it seriously, but even crying children will burst into laughter when they see Maschiff's face.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Mabosstiff
flavorText: Mabosstiff loves playing with children. Though usually gentle, it takes on an intimidating look when protecting its family.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Varoom
flavorText: It is said that this Pokémon was born when an unknown poison Pokémon entered and inspirited an engine left at a scrap-processing factory.
Attack1Text: Put up to 2 Basic Energy cards from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Revavroom
flavorText: It creates a gas out of poison and minerals from rocks. It then detonates the gas in its cylinders— now numbering eight—to generate energy.
Ability1Text: You must discard an Energy card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Iron Treads ex
Attack1Text: After doing damage, you may discard all Future Booster Energy Capsules from this Pokémon. If you do, during your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 150 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Gholdengo
flavorText: Its body seems to be made up of 1,000 coins. This Pokémon gets along well with others and is quick to make friends with anybody.
Attack1Text: You may attach any number of Basic Metal Energy cards from your hand to your Pokémon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin for each Metal Energy attached to this Pokémon. This attack does 80 damage for each heads.

name: Noibat
flavorText: This Pokémon emits ultrasonic waves from its large ears to search for fruit to eat. It mistakes Applin for its food.

name: Noivern ex
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from Basic Pokémon.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, they can't play any Special Energy or Stadium cards from their hand.

name: Cyclizar
flavorText: Apparently Cyclizar has been allowing people to ride on its back since ancient times. Depictions of this have been found in 10,000-year-old murals.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Lechonk
flavorText: It searches for food all day. It possesses a keen sense of smell but doesn't use it for anything other than foraging.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Oinkologne
flavorText: This Pokémon sends a flowerlike scent wafting about. Well-developed muscles in its legs allow it to leap more than 16 feet with no trouble at all.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. Put a number of cards up to the number of heads from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Tandemaus
flavorText: Exhibiting great teamwork, they use their incisors to cut pieces out of any material that might be useful for a nest, then make off with them.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.

name: Maushold
flavorText: The larger pair protects the little ones during battles. When facing strong opponents, the whole group will join the fight.
Attack2Text: This attack does 70 damage for each of your Maushold in play.

name: Squawkabilly ex
Ability1Text: Once during your first turn, you may discard your hand and draw 6 cards. You can't use more than 1 Squawk and Seize Ability during your turn.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Basic Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Technical Machine: Crisis Punch
Attack1Text: You can use this attack only when your opponent has exactly 1 Prize card remaining.

name: Oddish
flavorText: During the day, it stays in the cold underground to avoid the sun. It grows by bathing in moonlight.

name: Gloom
flavorText: What appears to be drool is actually sweet honey. It is very sticky and clings stubbornly if touched.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may look at the top 3 cards of your deck and attach any number of Basic Energy cards you find there to your Pokémon in any way you like. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

name: Vileplume
flavorText: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may look at the top 8 cards of your deck and attach any number of Basic Energy cards you find there to your Pokémon in any way you like. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

name: Scyther
flavorText: It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes, moving too fast for the human eye to track.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Hoppip
flavorText: This Pokémon is blown across vast distances by the wind. It is unclear where the Hoppip of Paldea originally came from.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Skiploom
flavorText: Skiploom enthusiasts can apparently tell where a Skiploom was born by the scent drifting from the flower on the Pokémon's head.
Ability1Text: If any damage is done to this Pokémon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Jumpluff
flavorText: Jumpluff travels on seasonal winds. Once its cotton spores run out, its journey ends, as does its life.
Ability1Text: If any damage is done to this Pokémon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Pineco
flavorText: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn't bother it.

name: Snover
flavorText: During cold seasons, it migrates to the mountain's lower reaches. It returns to the snow-covered summit in the spring.

name: Abomasnow
flavorText: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.
Ability1Text: Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) can't be healed.

name: Smoliv
flavorText: It protects itself from enemies by emitting oil from the fruit on its head. This oil is bitter and astringent enough to make someone flinch.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Dolliv
flavorText: Dolliv shares its tasty, fresh-scented oil with others. This species has coexisted with humans since times long gone.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, if the Defending Pokémon tries to attack, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack doesn't happen.

name: Arboliva
flavorText: This calm Pokémon is very compassionate. It will share its delicious, nutrient-rich oil with weakened Pokémon.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may heal all damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Toedscool
flavorText: Though it looks like Tentacool, Toedscool is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Capsakid
flavorText: Traditional Paldean dishes can be extremely spicy because they include the shed front teeth of Capsakid among their ingredients.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Fire Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Scovillain
flavorText: The red head converts spicy chemicals into fire energy and blasts the surrounding area with a super spicy stream of flame.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is in play, it is Grass and Fire type.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Rellor
flavorText: This Pokémon creates a mud ball by mixing sand and dirt with psychic energy. It treasures its mud ball more than its own life.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

name: Charmander
flavorText: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.
Attack1Text: Discard a Stadium in play.

name: Charmeleon
flavorText: If it becomes agitated during battle, it spouts intense flames, incinerating its surroundings.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks used by your opponent's Pokémon done to this Pokémon. (Damage is not an effect.)

name: Paldean Tauros
flavorText: People call this kind of Tauros the Blaze Breed due to the hot air it snorts from its nostrils. Its three tails are intertwined.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Entei
flavorText: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, attacks used by your opponent's Active Pokémon do 20 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Oricorio
flavorText: This Pokémon is incredibly popular, possibly because its passionate dancing is a great match with the temperament of Paldean people.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may heal 20 damage from your Active Evolution Pokémon.

name: Charcadet
flavorText: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokémon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.

name: Armarouge
flavorText: Armarouge evolved through the use of a set of armor that belonged to a distinguished warrior. This Pokémon is incredibly loyal.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may move a Fire Energy from 1 of your Benched Pokémon to your Active Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Slowpoke
flavorText: It is always vacantly lost in thought, but no one knows what it is thinking about. It is good at fishing with its tail.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon is now Asleep. Heal 30 damage from it.

name: Slowbro
flavorText: If the tail-biting Shellder is thrown off in a harsh battle, this Pokémon reverts to being an ordinary Slowpoke.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your other Pokémon to this Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Staryu
flavorText: Fish Pokémon nibble at it, but Staryu isn't bothered. Its body regenerates quickly, even if part of it is completely torn off.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance, or by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Starmie
flavorText: Starmie swims by spinning its body at high speed. As this Pokémon cruises through the ocean, it absorbs tiny plankton.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. If you placed any damage counters in this way, discard this Pokémon and all attached cards.

name: Paldean Tauros
flavorText: It swims by jetting water from its horns. The most notable characteristic of the Aqua Breed is its high body fat, which allows it to float easily.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Wiglett
flavorText: This Pokémon can pick up the scent of a Veluza just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in the sand.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Wugtrio
flavorText: It has a vicious temperament, contrary to what its appearance may suggest. It wraps its long bodies around prey, then drags the prey into its den.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. For each heads, discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.

name: Finizen
flavorText: It likes playing with others of its kind using the water ring on its tail. It uses ultrasonic waves to sense the emotions of other living creatures.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. If you do, search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon and put it onto this Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Palafin
flavorText: This Pokémon's ancient genes have awakened. It is now so extraordinarily strong that it can easily lift a cruise ship with one fin.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon didn't move from the Bench to the Active Spot this turn, this attack does nothing.

name: Veluza
flavorText: When Veluza discards unnecessary flesh, its mind becomes honed and its psychic power increases. The spare flesh has a mild but delicious flavor.
Attack2Text: If you have no cards in your hand, this attack can be used for Water.

name: Dondozo
flavorText: This Pokémon is a glutton, but it's bad at getting food. It teams up with a Tatsugiri to catch prey.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage for each Tatsugiri in your discard pile.

name: Tatsugiri
flavorText: This is a small dragon Pokémon. It lives inside the mouth of Dondozo to protect itself from enemies on the outside.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Water Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Basic Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Put this Pokémon and all attached cards into your hand.

name: Frigibax
flavorText: Frigibax absorbs heat through its dorsal fin and converts the heat into ice energy. The higher the temperature, the more energy Frigibax stores.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Arctibax
flavorText: Arctibax freezes the air around it, protecting its face with an ice mask and turning its dorsal fin into a blade of ice.

name: Baxcalibur
flavorText: This Pokémon blasts cryogenic air out from its mouth. This air can instantly freeze even liquid-hot lava.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may attach a Basic Water Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: ﻿When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon's attacks do 20 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Raichu
flavorText: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.
Ability1Text: When 1 of your Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, you may move a Lightning Energy from that Pokémon to this Pokémon.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 50 damage to itself.

name: Voltorb
flavorText: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Electrode
flavorText: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.
Attack1Text: Before doing damage, you may discard any number of Pokémon Tools from your Pokémon. This attack does 40 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Shinx
flavorText: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Luxio
flavorText: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

name: Luxray
flavorText: It can see clearly through walls to track down its prey and seek its lost young.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in your hand and you have more Prize cards remaining than your opponent, you may put this Pokémon onto your Bench.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

name: Pachirisu
flavorText: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.
Ability1Text: This Pokémon can't be Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your Benched Lightning Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness.

name: Thundurus
flavorText: As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, prevent all damage done to your Benched Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 90 damage to itself.

name: Toxel
flavorText: It has no problem drinking dirty water. An organ inside Toxel's body filters such water into a poisonous liquid that is harmless to Toxel.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Toxtricity
flavorText: Many youths admire the way this Pokémon listlessly picks fights and keeps its cool no matter what opponent it faces.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each different type of Pokémon on your Bench.

name: Pawmi
flavorText: The pads of its paws are electricity-discharging organs. Pawmi fires electricity from its forepaws while standing unsteadily on its hind legs.

name: Pawmo
flavorText: Pawmo uses a unique fighting technique in which it uses its forepaws to strike foes and zap them with electricity from its paw pads simultaneously.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Pawmot
flavorText: Pawmot's fluffy fur acts as a battery. It can store the same amount of electricity as an electric car.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Basic Lightning Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Wattrel
flavorText: When its wings catch the wind, the bones within produce electricity. This Pokémon dives into the ocean, catching prey by electrocuting them.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile that has the United Wings attack.

name: Kilowattrel
flavorText: Kilowattrel inflates its throat sac to amplify its electricity. By riding the wind, this Pokémon can fly over 430 miles in a day.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile that has the United Wings attack to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Wigglytuff
flavorText: It has a very fine fur. Take care not to make it angry, or it may inflate steadily and hit with a body slam.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Therapeutic Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Abra
flavorText: Abra can teleport in its sleep. Apparently the more deeply Abra sleeps, the farther its teleportations go.

name: Kadabra
flavorText: This Pokémon's telekinesis is immensely powerful. To prepare for evolution, Kadabra stores up psychic energy in the star on its forehead.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Cleffa
flavorText: Because of its unusual, starlike silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.
Attack1Text: Draw cards until you have 7 cards in your hand.

name: Natu
flavorText: Because its wings aren't yet fully grown, it has to hop to get around. It is always staring at something.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Xatu
flavorText: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun's movement all day.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Basic Psychic Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. If you attached Energy to a Pokémon in this way, draw 2 cards.

name: Ralts
flavorText: The horns on its head provide a strong power that enables it to sense people's emotions.

name: Kirlia
flavorText: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Drifloon
flavorText: It is whispered that any child who mistakes Drifloon for a balloon and holds on to it could wind up missing.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

name: Drifblim
flavorText: It can generate and release gas within its body. That's how it can control the altitude of its drift.
Attack2Text: Put 8 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.

name: Mime Jr.
flavorText: In an attempt to confuse its enemy, it mimics the enemy's movements. Then it wastes no time in making itself scarce!
Attack1Text: Your opponent chooses an attack from 1 of their Pokémon in play. Use the chosen attack as this attack.

name: Spiritomb
flavorText: Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.
Ability1Text: Basic Pokémon V in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Abilities.
Attack1Text: Put this Pokémon and all attached cards into your hand.

name: Klefki
flavorText: In the past, noble families entrusted their vault keys to a Klefki. They passed the Klefki down through the generations, taking good care of it.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, Basic Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Abilities, except for Mischievous Lock.
Attack1Text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Mimikyu
flavorText: This Pokémon lives in dark places untouched by sunlight. When it appears before humans, it hides itself under a cloth that resembles a Pikachu.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon ex and Pokémon V.
Attack1Text: Put 7 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Dachsbun
flavorText: The pleasant aroma that emanates from this Pokémon's body helps wheat grow, so Dachsbun has been treasured by farming villages.
Ability1Text: This Pokémon can't be Burned. Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Fire Pokémon.

name: Ceruledge
flavorText: The fiery blades on its arms burn fiercely with the lingering resentment of a sword wielder who fell before accomplishing their goal.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex or Pokémon V, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Rabsca
flavorText: The body that supports the ball barely moves. Therefore, it is thought that the true body of this Pokémon is actually inside the ball.
Attack1Text: Put a Pokémon from your discard pile onto your Bench.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Flittle
flavorText: Flittle's toes levitate about half an inch above the ground because of the psychic power emitted from the frills on the Pokémon's belly.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Tinkatink
flavorText: It swings its handmade hammer around to protect itself, but the hammer is often stolen by Pokémon that eat metal.
Attack1Text: Put an Item card from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Tinkatuff
flavorText: This Pokémon will attack groups of Pawniard and Bisharp, gathering metal from them in order to create a large and sturdy hammer.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Tinkaton
flavorText: This intelligent Pokémon has a very daring disposition. It knocks rocks into the sky with its hammer, aiming for flying Corviknight.
Ability1Text: You must discard a card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw 3 cards.
Attack1Text: If this Pokémon has any Special Energy attached, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Houndstone
flavorText: A lovingly mourned Pokémon was reborn as Houndstone. It doesn't like anyone touching the protuberance atop its head.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each Psychic Pokémon in your discard pile.

name: Mankey
flavorText: It is extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment, then thrashing away the next instant.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Primeape
flavorText: Some researchers theorize that Primeape remains angry even when inside a Poké Ball.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

name: Annihilape
flavorText: It imbues its fists with the power of the rage that it kept hidden in its heart. Opponents struck by these imbued fists will be shattered to their core.
Attack1Text: This attack does 70 damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 50 damage to itself.

name: Paldean Tauros
flavorText: This kind of Tauros, known as the Combat Breed, is distinguished by its thick, powerful muscles and its fierce disposition.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Riolu
flavorText: They communicate with one another using their auras. They are able to run all through the night.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

name: Lucario
flavorText: It's said that no foe can remain invisible to Lucario, since it can detect auras—even those of foes it could not otherwise see.
Attack1Text: If any of your Fighting Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does 120 more damage.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Accelerating Stab.

name: Hawlucha
flavorText: Its elegant finishing moves—performed by nimbly leaping around using its wings—are polished in the forest where it was born and raised.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may choose 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon and put 1 damage counter on each of them.

name: Nacli
flavorText: It was born in a layer of rock salt deep under the earth. This species was particularly treasured in the old days, as they would share precious salt.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Naclstack
flavorText: This Pokémon dry cures its prey by spraying salt over them. The curing process steals away the water in the prey's body.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 60 damage for each heads.

name: Garganacl
flavorText: Garganacl will rub its fingertips together and sprinkle injured Pokémon with salt. Even severe wounds will promptly heal afterward.
Ability1Text: During Pokémon Checkup, heal 20 damage from each of your Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Glimmet
flavorText: It absorbs nutrients from cave walls. The petals it wears are made of crystallized poison.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon and put it onto this Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Paldean Wooper
flavorText: After losing a territorial struggle, Wooper began living on land. The Pokémon changed over time, developing a poisonous film to protect its body.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Stadium card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Murkrow
flavorText: Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile that has the United Wings attack.

name: Sneasel
flavorText: This cunning Pokémon hides under the cover of darkness, waiting to attack its prey.

name: Weavile
flavorText: Evolution made it even more devious. It communicates by clawing signs in boulders.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, when this Pokémon moves from your Bench to the Active Spot, you may switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Basic Pokémon to the Active Spot.

name: Sableye
flavorText: It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Pawniard
flavorText: Pawniard will fearlessly challenge even powerful foes. In a pinch, it will cling to opponents and pierce them with the blades all over its body.

name: Bisharp
flavorText: This Pokémon commands a group of several Pawniard. Groups that are defeated in territorial disputes are absorbed by the winning side.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Kingambit
flavorText: Only a Bisharp that stands above all others in its vast army can evolve into Kingambit.
Ability1Text: Your Basic Pokémon's attacks do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Mabosstiff
flavorText: Mabosstiff loves playing with children. Though usually gentle, it takes on an intimidating look when protecting its family.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Shroodle
flavorText: Though usually a mellow Pokémon, it will sink its sharp, poison-soaked front teeth into any that anger it, causing paralysis in the object of its ire.
Attack1Text: Put a Basic Energy card from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Grafaiai
flavorText: The color of the poisonous saliva depends on what the Pokémon eats. Grafaiai covers its fingers in its saliva and draws patterns on trees in forests.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: You may discard as many Basic Energy cards as you like from your hand. This attack does 40 damage for each type of Basic Energy you discarded in this way.

name: Scizor
flavorText: This Pokémon's pincers, which contain steel, can crush any hard object they get ahold of into bits.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each of your opponent's Pokémon in play that has an Ability.

name: Varoom
flavorText: It is said that this Pokémon was born when an unknown poison Pokémon entered and inspirited an engine left at a scrap-processing factory.
Attack1Text: Put up to 2 Basic Energy cards from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Revavroom
flavorText: It creates a gas out of poison and minerals from rocks. It then detonates the gas in its cylinders— now numbering eight—to generate energy.
Ability1Text: You must discard an Energy card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Noibat
flavorText: This Pokémon emits ultrasonic waves from its large ears to search for fruit to eat. It mistakes Applin for its food.

name: Cyclizar
flavorText: Apparently Cyclizar has been allowing people to ride on its back since ancient times. Depictions of this have been found in 10,000-year-old murals.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Pidgey
flavorText: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Pidgeotto
flavorText: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this Pokémon will fiercely peck at any intruder.

name: Jigglypuff
flavorText: When its huge eyes waver, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Doduo
flavorText: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Dodrio
flavorText: An odd species that is rarely found. The three heads respectively represent joy, sadness, and anger.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may put 1 damage counter on this Pokémon. If you do, draw a card.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

name: Ditto
flavorText: Its transformation ability is perfect. However, if made to laugh, it can't maintain its disguise.
Ability1Text: Once during your first turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may search your deck and choose a Basic Pokémon you find there, except any Ditto. If you do, discard this Pokémon and all attached cards, and put the chosen Pokémon in its place. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Snorlax
flavorText: This Pokémon's stomach is so strong, even eating moldy or rotten food will not affect it.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may put up to 2 Leftovers cards from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Wingull
flavorText: It soars high in the sky, riding on updrafts like a glider. It carries food tucked in its bill.

name: Pelipper
flavorText: It is a flying transporter that carries small Pokémon in its beak. It bobs on the waves to rest its wings.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may choose 1: put a Supporter card from your discard pile into your hand; or search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, put it into your hand, and then shuffle your deck.

name: Skwovet
flavorText: No matter how much it stuffs its belly with food, it is always anxious about getting hungry again. So, it stashes berries in its cheeks and tail.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may shuffle your hand and put it on the bottom of your deck. If you put any cards on the bottom of your deck in this way, draw a card.

name: Greedent
flavorText: This Pokémon makes off with heaps of fallen berries by wrapping them in its tail, which is roughly twice the length of its body.
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Lechonk
flavorText: It searches for food all day. It possesses a keen sense of smell but doesn't use it for anything other than foraging.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Oinkologne
flavorText: This Pokémon sends a flowerlike scent wafting about. Well-developed muscles in its legs allow it to leap more than 16 feet with no trouble at all.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. Put a number of cards up to the number of heads from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Tandemaus
flavorText: Exhibiting great teamwork, they use their incisors to cut pieces out of any material that might be useful for a nest, then make off with them.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.

name: Maushold
flavorText: The larger pair protects the little ones during battles. When facing strong opponents, the whole group will join the fight.
Attack2Text: This attack does 70 damage for each of your Maushold in play.

name: Flamigo
flavorText: This Pokémon apparently ties the base of its neck into a knot so that energy stored in its belly does not escape from its beak.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 3 Flamigo, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile that has the United Wings attack.

name: Forretress ex
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 5 Basic Grass Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck. If you searched your deck in this way, this Pokémon is Knocked Out.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Toedscruel ex
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks used by your opponent's Pokémon done to all of your Pokémon that have Energy attached. (Existing effects are not removed. Damage is not an effect.)
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon that has any Grass Energy attached.

name: Espathra ex
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, attacks used by your opponent's Active Pokémon cost Colorless more.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to both Active Pokémon.

name: Alakazam ex
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack can be used even if this Pokémon is on the Bench.

name: Mew ex
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 3 cards in your hand.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack.

name: Gardevoir ex
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may attach a Basic Psychic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Psychic Pokémon. If you attached Energy to a Pokémon in this way, put 2 damage counters on that Pokémon. You can't use this Ability on a Pokémon that would be Knocked Out.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon recovers from all Special Conditions.

name: Glimmora ex
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent can't have more than 3 Benched Pokémon. If they have 4 or more Benched Pokémon, they discard Benched Pokémon until they have 3 Pokémon on the Bench. If more than one effect changes the number of Benched Pokémon allowed, use the smaller number.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Paldean Clodsire ex
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if a Stadium is in play, you may make your opponent's Active Pokémon Poisoned.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, during your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Noivern ex
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from Basic Pokémon.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, they can't play any Special Energy or Stadium cards from their hand.

name: Pidgeot ex
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. You can't use more than 1 Quick Search Ability each turn.
Attack1Text: You may discard a Stadium in play.

name: Wigglytuff ex
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon has any Special Energy attached, it gets +100 HP.
Attack1Text: If you played a Supporter card from your hand during this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Squawkabilly ex
Ability1Text: Once during your first turn, you may discard your hand and draw 6 cards. You can't use more than 1 Squawk and Seize Ability during your turn.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Basic Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Wugtrio
flavorText: It has a vicious temperament, contrary to what its appearance may suggest. It wraps its long bodies around prey, then drags the prey into its den.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. For each heads, discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.

name: Palafin
flavorText: This Pokémon's ancient genes have awakened. It is now so extraordinarily strong that it can easily lift a cruise ship with one fin.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon didn't move from the Bench to the Active Spot this turn, this attack does nothing.

name: Pawmi
flavorText: The pads of its paws are electricity-discharging organs. Pawmi fires electricity from its forepaws while standing unsteadily on its hind legs.

name: Mew ex
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 3 cards in your hand.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack.

name: Gardevoir ex
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may attach a Basic Psychic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Psychic Pokémon. If you attached Energy to a Pokémon in this way, put 2 damage counters on that Pokémon. You can't use this Ability on a Pokémon that would be Knocked Out.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon recovers from all Special Conditions.

name: Charizard ex
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 3 Basic Fire Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

name: Wo-Chien ex
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon for each Prize card your opponent has taken. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Chi-Yu ex
Attack1Text: Discard the top 2 cards of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: Choose up to 3 of your Benched Pokémon. For each of those Pokémon, search your deck for a Basic Fire Energy card and attach it to that Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Chien-Pao ex
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may search your deck for up to 2 Basic Water Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: You may discard any amount of Water Energy from your Pokémon. This attack does 60 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Miraidon ex
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 Basic Lightning Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Ting-Lu ex
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent's Pokémon in play that have any damage counters on them have no Abilities, except for Pokémon ex.
Attack1Text: Put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

name: Koraidon ex
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may attach up to 2 Basic Fighting Energy cards from your discard pile to your Basic Fighting Pokémon in any way you like. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.
